      • getDataList

        public java.lang.String getDataList()
        Gets the form's data list on completion of the form. The data list must be a well-formed XML string representing the expected data structure for the work item or case start. The opening and closing tag must be the name of task of which the work item is an instance, or of the root net name of the case instance.
        Specified by:
        getDataList in interface DynamicForm
        Returns:
        A well-formed XML String of the work item's output data values

      • getDocComponentIDs

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Long> getDocComponentIDs()
        Description copied from interface: DynamicForm
        Gets a list of component identifiers that represent documents managed by the doc store service. Only for case-level forms. When a document is uploaded to the Document Store at case start, the upload occurs before the case has been launched and thus there is not yet a case id allocated. Once the case launch is successful, this method should be called to associate the case id with the already uploaded document.
        Specified by:
        getDocComponentIDs in interface DynamicForm
        Returns:
        a List of Long identifiers
